1. Margherita Pizza:

Ingredients:

1 pizza dough
1/2 cup pizza sauce
2 cups mozzarella cheese, shredded
Fresh basil leaves
Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions:

Preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C).
Roll out the pizza dough (after adding flour to your hands) on a floured surface to your desired thickness.
Transfer the dough to a pizza stone or baking sheet.
Spread the pizza sauce evenly over the dough, leaving a small border around the edges.
Sprinkle the shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is bubbly.
Remove from the oven and garnish with fresh basil leaves.
Slice and serve hot.
